    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix infinite loop in itti_send_msg_to_task when using no_itti mode\n\n### Summary\nWhen running OAI5G in no_itti mode (single-threaded), the `itti_send_msg_to_task()` function enters an infinite loop because it repeatedly calls the shortcut function without consuming messages from the queue.\n\n### Changes\n- `common/utils/ocp_itti/intertask_interface.cpp`: Replaced the while loop in `itti_send_msg_to_task()` with a single call to the shortcut function when processing messages in no_itti mode.\n\n### Reproduction\nTo reproduce this issue:\n1. Start OAI5G gNB with `--no-itti-threads` flag\n2. Trigger any RRC connection establishment procedure\n3. Observe that the process becomes unresponsive due to infinite loop in message processing\n4. CPU usage will spike to 100% and no further processing occurs\n\nThe symptom is that the gNB appears to hang after receiving the first UE message, with no RRC responses being sent back to the UE.\n"
}